  <title>Phase</title>
  <p>
    <term>Phase</term> is an additional attribute that is relevant when a qubit is in superposition.
    In the last section, you saw that if you have a circuit with two consecutive <c>H</c> gates,
    then the qubit goes into a superposition state after the <em>first</em>
    <c>H</c> gate, but then
    it goes back to its original state after the <em>second</em>
    <c>H</c> gate.
    When in a superposition state, the two qubits have opposite phase.
  </p>

  <sidebyside widths="75% 25%" valign="top">
    <p>
      Now we are going to explore a gate that affects the phase of the qubit.
      Use the following circuit to determine how the <c>Z</c> gate affects a qubit
      that is in the state <m>\ket{0}</m> or <m>\ket{1}</m>.
    </p>
